{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Dinero withdrawal finalization condition is inverted","locations":["withdraws/Dinero.sol:55","withdraws/Dinero.sol:71","withdraws/Dinero.sol:87"],"claim":"`DineroWithdrawRequestManager.canFinalizeWithdrawRequest` returns `PirexETH.outstandingRedemptions() > totalAssets`, but finalization readiness should require sufficient assets for redemptions. The comparison is inverted.","impact":"Dinero withdraw requests can remain unfinalizable even when they should be redeemable, leaving funds stuck in pending-withdraw state.","paths":["User initiates a Dinero withdrawal request","Referenced batches become dissolved/slashed and assets are available","Outstanding redemptions are less than or equal to request assets","Readiness check still returns false due to inverted comparison, blocking finalize/redeem"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Morpho market oracle uses account-agnostic vault price and can misprice pending-withdraw collateral","locations":["routers/MorphoLendingRouter.sol:64","AbstractYieldStrategy.sol:118","AbstractYieldStrategy.sol:123","staking/AbstractStakingStrategy.sol:50","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:300"],"claim":"Morpho markets are configured with `oracle: vault`, so Morpho-side checks depend on the vault oracle path. Borrower-specific pending-withdraw valuation adjustments rely on borrower context (`price(address)` / `t_CurrentAccount`) and may be skipped in account-agnostic oracle reads.","impact":"Collateral can be overvalued for borrowers with pending withdraws, enabling excess borrowing and delayed liquidation, increasing bad-debt risk.","paths":["Borrower enters pending-withdraw state where account-specific valuation should apply","Morpho operations rely on market oracle configured as the vault","Oracle read path is account-agnostic and may not apply borrower-specific pending-withdraw haircut","Borrow/solvency checks can overestimate collateral value"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"LP zero-balance legs create missing withdraw requests that break pending valuation and finalization","locations":["single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:332","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:363","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:370","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:392"],"claim":"LP withdraw initiation skips legs with `exitBalances[i] == 0`, creating no request for those legs. Later logic assumes every leg has a request: valuation path requires `hasRequest`, and finalization computes `yieldTokensBurned = w.yieldTokenAmount * sharesToRedeem / w.sharesAmount` even when `w.sharesAmount == 0` for skipped legs.","impact":"Pending-withdraw positions can become unpriceable and matured requests can revert during redemption, disrupting solvency checks and potentially locking exits.","paths":["A proportional LP exit returns zero amount for at least one pool token leg","initiateWithdraw skips request creation for that leg","Account remains pending due to other legs","Valuation reverts on `require(hasRequest)` or finalization reverts on division by zero"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Reward debt is advanced even when reward transfer fails","locations":["rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:231","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:232","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:242","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:250"],"claim":"`_claimRewardToken` updates account `rewardDebt` before attempting transfer, then swallows transfer failures and emits a zero-transfer event. Failed transfers do not preserve claimable rewards.","impact":"Users can permanently lose accrued rewards when transfer fails (blacklist, paused/broken token, non-standard behavior) because accounting is not rolled back.","paths":["User claims rewards","Contract computes `rewardToClaim` and updates `rewardDebt`","Reward token transfer fails or returns false","Function emits zero transfer but keeps updated debt, burning claim"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Zero-yield-token withdraw requests can trigger division-by-zero on finalization accounting","locations":["AbstractYieldStrategy.sol:302","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:111","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:114","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:240","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:326"],"claim":"Withdraw initiation does not enforce `yieldTokenAmount > 0`. For dust shares, `convertSharesToYieldToken` can round to zero, creating requests with nonzero shares but `totalYieldTokenAmount == 0`; finalized accounting later divides by `s.totalYieldTokenAmount`.","impact":"Dust positions can be pushed into withdraw-request states that fail to finalize/redeem cleanly.","paths":["Account with very small shares initiates withdraw","`convertSharesToYieldToken` rounds down to zero","Request is recorded with `yieldTokenAmount == 0` and tokenized total set to zero","Finalized pro-rata calculation divides by zero and reverts"],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Ethena zero-duration cooldown mode strands redeemed USDe in cloned holder","locations":["withdraws/Ethena.sol:18","withdraws/Ethena.sol:20","withdraws/Ethena.sol:39","withdraws/Ethena.sol:47"],"claim":"If `sUSDe.cooldownDuration() == 0`, `_startCooldown` redeems immediately into the holder. During finalization, `_finalizeCooldown` computes `balanceAfter - balanceBefore` after funds are already present, so `tokensClaimed` becomes zero and redeemed USDe is not forwarded to the vault.","impact":"Withdrawals can finalize with zero payout while user funds remain trapped in per-request holder clones until admin rescue.","paths":["Ethena cooldown duration is set to zero","Withdraw initiation redeems sUSDe directly into the cloned holder","Finalization computes delta balance after funds already arrived","`tokensClaimed` is zero and user receives nothing"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Dinero withdrawals never request validator exits","locations":["withdraws/Dinero.sol:29","withdraws/Dinero.sol:30"],"claim":"Dinero withdrawal initiation hardcodes `shouldTriggerValidatorExit = false` in `PirexETH.initiateRedemption`, so this flow never requests validator exits even when exits are needed to satisfy redemptions.","impact":"Requests can remain pending much longer and may be effectively stuck until external actors trigger exits or provide liquidity.","paths":["User initiates Dinero withdraw during low available redemption liquidity","Manager initiates redemption with `shouldTriggerValidatorExit = false`","No validator exit is requested by this flow","Finalization depends on external actors and can remain unavailable"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Dinero request-id nonce overflows after 65,535 withdrawals and halts new requests","locations":["withdraws/Dinero.sol:10","withdraws/Dinero.sol:32"],"claim":"Dinero uses a `uint16` `s_batchNonce` for request-id uniqueness. Under Solidity 0.8 checked arithmetic, `++s_batchNonce` reverts after `type(uint16).max`.","impact":"A finite number of withdrawals can exhaust nonce space and permanently DoS new Dinero withdraw requests unless code is upgraded.","paths":["Repeated withdraw initiations increment `s_batchNonce`","Nonce reaches 65,535","Next `++s_batchNonce` overflows and reverts","All subsequent Dinero withdraw initiations fail"],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Router transfer authorization is not bound to the intended source account","locations":["AbstractYieldStrategy.sol:219","AbstractYieldStrategy.sol:333"],"claim":"`allowTransfer` authorizes only destination and amount in transient storage, but `_update` does not verify `from`. While the transient authorization is live, any transfer to the authorized `to` for up to the authorized amount is accepted, regardless of sender address.","impact":"The invariant that native balances cannot be transferred can be bypassed in router-mediated transfer windows, enabling misdirected share movement from unintended holders if a spender already has allowance.","paths":["Router calls `allowTransfer(receiver, amount, currentAccount)`","Authorized spender/market executes transfer path to `receiver` with `from` not equal to intended account","Vault accepts transfer because `_update` checks only `to` and `amount`","Unintended holder shares can be moved"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Any whitelisted lending router can delete another router's live position record","locations":["proxy/AddressRegistry.sol:144"],"claim":"`clearPosition` only checks that caller is a whitelisted lending router, then unconditionally deletes `accountPositions[account][vault]`. It does not require caller to match the router recorded in that position.","impact":"A buggy or compromised whitelisted router can erase another router's position record, breaking position ownership invariants, blocking normal exit checks on the legitimate router, and enabling conflicting re-entry records.","paths":["Router A opens position for account/vault","Router B (also whitelisted) calls `clearPosition(account, vault)`","Registry entry is deleted despite Router A being owner","Router A `exitPosition` fails `_checkExit` and account can create inconsistent new router state"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Low","confidence":"low","title":"Sequencer outage protection is skipped on legacy oracle accessors","locations":["oracles/AbstractCustomOracle.sol:51","oracles/AbstractCustomOracle.sol:62","oracles/AbstractCustomOracle.sol:66","oracles/AbstractCustomOracle.sol:70"],"claim":"Sequencer/grace-period checks are enforced only in `latestRoundData()`. Legacy Chainlink-style getters (`latestAnswer`, `latestTimestamp`, `latestRound`) return `_calculateBaseToQuote()` directly without `_checkSequencer()`.","impact":"Consumers using legacy accessor methods can read prices during sequencer downtime/grace periods, bypassing intended outage safety checks.","paths":["Sequencer is down or in grace period","Consumer calls `latestAnswer()`/`latestTimestamp()`/`latestRound()` instead of `latestRoundData()`","Oracle returns values without sequencer safety gate"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Permissionless manual finalization can lock in GenericERC4626 withdrawals early and strip later share appreciation","locations":["withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:149","withdraws/GenericERC4626.sol:32","withdraws/GenericERC4626.sol:42"],"claim":"`finalizeRequestManual` is permissionless, and `GenericERC4626WithdrawRequestManager` always reports requests as finalizable and redeems ERC4626 shares immediately in `_finalizeWithdrawImpl`. Any third party can force conversion of a pending request from yield-bearing ERC4626 shares into idle underlying before the requester chooses to redeem.","impact":"A user can be forced to stop earning ERC4626 share-price appreciation after request initiation, creating a griefing vector that causes measurable underpayment versus waiting to redeem later.","paths":["User initiates withdraw via `GenericERC4626WithdrawRequestManager`","Before user exits, a third party calls `finalizeRequestManual(vault, user)`","Manager redeems request shares immediately and marks tokenized request finalized","User later redeems fixed underlying amount and misses subsequent ERC4626 appreciation"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-014","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Partial redemption of finalized tokenized withdraw requests can strand permanent rounding dust","locations":["withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:123","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:135","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:223","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:240"],"claim":"Finalized payout attribution uses floor division in `_finalizeWithdraw` (`totalWithdraw * yieldTokenAmount / totalYieldTokenAmount`) and partial redemption applies additional floor division. Residual remainders are never tracked for last-claimer settlement, so split redemptions can leave part of `totalWithdraw` unclaimable.","impact":"Small but permanent underpayment can accumulate across partial or tokenized redemptions, leaving withdraw-token dust stranded in the manager contract.","paths":["Request finalizes with `totalWithdraw` not exactly divisible by `totalYieldTokenAmount`","Request is redeemed through multiple partial burns/tokenized holders","Each redemption rounds down its pro-rata payout","Cumulative payouts end below `totalWithdraw` and remainder stays stuck"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"Low","confidence":"low","title":"Executed proxy upgrade state is not cleared, allowing potential same-implementation `executeUpgrade` replay","locations":["proxy/TimelockUpgradeableProxy.sol:40","proxy/TimelockUpgradeableProxy.sol:54","proxy/TimelockUpgradeableProxy.sol:58"],"claim":"After `executeUpgrade`, the proxy keeps `newImplementation` and `upgradeValidAt` populated. If `ERC1967Utils.upgradeToAndCall` permits invoking with the already-active implementation, upgrade admin can repeatedly call `executeUpgrade(data)` without re-running `initiateUpgrade` and waiting a new delay.","impact":"Timelock protection may degrade to a one-time wait, after which additional privileged delegatecall payloads on the same implementation can execute immediately.","paths":["Upgrade admin calls `initiateUpgrade(X)` and waits 7 days","Admin executes `executeUpgrade(data1)` successfully","Pending upgrade fields remain valid","Admin calls `executeUpgrade(data2)` again against same `newImplementation` with no fresh delay"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Curve V2 liquidation precheck can make LP vault positions unliquidatable","locations":["single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:253","single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:82","single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:146","single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:156"],"claim":"`_preLiquidation` calls `_checkReentrancyContext`, and the Curve V2 implementation performs `remove_liquidity(1, ...)` from the standalone `LP_LIB` contract (non-delegatecall path). Because `LP_LIB` normally holds no LP tokens, this precheck reverts and blocks liquidation before Morpho liquidation logic runs.","impact":"Underwater positions in affected Curve V2 LP vaults can become effectively unliquidatable, allowing bad debt to persist or grow.","paths":["Borrower opens leveraged position in a Curve V2 `CurveConvex2Token` vault","Position becomes liquidatable","Liquidator calls router `liquidate`","Vault `preLiquidation` executes `_checkReentrancyContext`","`LP_LIB` calls `remove_liquidity(1, ...)` without LP balance and reverts, blocking liquidation"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Account reward updates use stale accumulator values after vault reward claims","locations":["rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:158","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:159","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:168","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:173","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:209","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:267"],"claim":"`updateAccountRewards` snapshots `VaultRewardState[]` into memory, then `_claimVaultRewards` updates storage accumulators. Account claim/debt updates continue using stale memory accumulators; for emission-enabled tokens, `_accumulateSecondaryRewardViaEmissionRate` can overwrite storage with stale values and erase just-claimed reward deltas.","impact":"Rewards are misallocated: new entrants can capture pre-existing rewards, exiting users can miss rewards, and some claimed reward tokens can become unallocated in the vault.","paths":["External pool rewards accrue while accumulator is stale","`updateAccountRewards` copies state to memory","`_claimVaultRewards` claims rewards and updates storage accumulator","`_claimRewardToken` and later writes use stale memory accumulator","Users are overpaid/underpaid and claimed tokens may be stranded"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-018","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Force-claim delay enables just-in-time deposits to capture already-accrued pool rewards","locations":["rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:191","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:232","rewards/RewardManagerMixin.sol:72","rewards/RewardManagerMixin.sol:90"],"claim":"When `forceClaimAfter` prevents `_claimVaultRewards` from claiming external pool rewards, mint/burn flows still update account reward debt using old accumulators. Once claims are allowed, previously accrued rewards are distributed across the enlarged post-deposit supply.","impact":"Attackers can time entries before claim windows to dilute incumbents and extract a share of rewards earned before they provided capital.","paths":["Rewards accrue in external pool","`forceClaimAfter` causes account updates to skip claims","Attacker deposits before claim window opens","Claim is triggered after window and distributes old rewards over current supply","Attacker receives a share of historical rewards"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-019","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Reward-pool migration can claim old-pool rewards without allocating them to users","locations":["rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:47","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:51","rewards/AbstractRewardManager.sol:191","rewards/ConvexRewardManager.sol:19"],"claim":"`migrateRewardPool` first calls `_claimVaultRewards`, but this can early-return due to `forceClaimAfter`. Convex migration then executes `withdrawAndUnwrap(..., true)`, which claims old-pool rewards without running the vault balance-delta accumulator update path.","impact":"Rewards claimed during migration can remain in the vault balance but never enter `accumulatedRewardPerVaultShare`, leaving users unable to claim them.","paths":["Old reward pool has accrued rewards","Admin migrates before `lastClaimTimestamp + forceClaimAfter`","`_claimVaultRewards` returns early","`withdrawAndUnwrap(..., true)` claims rewards during unstake","Claimed tokens are not added to user reward accumulator"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-020","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Curve ETH-leg async withdraw uses address(0) manager key after ETH is wrapped to WETH","locations":["single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:54","single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:59","single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:205","single-sided-lp/CurveConvex2Token.sol:207","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:359","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:364","single-sided-lp/AbstractSingleSidedLP.sol:368"],"claim":"Curve native ETH legs are stored as `address(0)` in `TOKENS()`. During exit, ETH is wrapped to WETH when the vault asset is WETH, but async-withdraw initiation still resolves withdraw manager by the original `address(0)` token key, leading to invalid manager calls for nonzero ETH legs.","impact":"Async withdraw initiation (and dependent pending-withdraw flows) can revert for Curve pools with native ETH legs, potentially trapping positions from entering withdraw request flow.","paths":["Curve pool token list includes native ETH","WETH-denominated vault performs proportional exit for async withdraw","Exit path wraps ETH leg into WETH","Withdraw loop still queries manager with `address(0)` leg token","Manager call for that leg reverts or is unusable"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-021","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Ethena pending-withdraw valuation prices fixed USDe claim as yield-bearing sUSDe","locations":["withdraws/Ethena.sol:16","withdraws/Ethena.sol:22","withdraws/Ethena.sol:94","withdraws/Ethena.sol:98","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:327","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:329","withdraws/AbstractWithdrawRequestManager.sol:331"],"claim":"Starting Ethena cooldown converts sUSDe shares into a fixed USDe claim, but unfinalized valuation still prices `w.yieldTokenAmount` at current sUSDe rate via `YIELD_TOKEN` pricing until finalization.","impact":"As sUSDe appreciates during cooldown, pending-withdraw collateral is overstated, distorting health checks and delaying liquidations.","paths":["Borrower initiates Ethena withdraw request","Cooldown fixes eventual USDe claim amount","sUSDe exchange rate increases before finalization","`getWithdrawRequestValue` prices unfinalized request using current sUSDe rate","Borrower collateral value is overstated versus realizable claim"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-022","severity":"Low","confidence":"low","title":"Dinero finalization credits nominal upxETH amounts instead of measured redeemed ETH","locations":["withdraws/Dinero.sol:60","withdraws/Dinero.sol:63","withdraws/Dinero.sol:64","withdraws/Dinero.sol:68","withdraws/Dinero.sol:78"],"claim":"`_finalizeWithdrawImpl` increments `tokensClaimed` by ERC1155 `upxETH` nominal balance and does not measure ETH balance deltas from `redeemWithUpxEth`. With slashed batches allowed as finalizable, any mismatch between nominal and actual ETH redeemed can break downstream WETH wrapping/accounting.","impact":"Finalization can revert or misaccount withdrawal proceeds in edge cases where redemption output differs from nominal upxETH units.","paths":["Request includes dissolved/slashed batches","Manager redeems per-batch `upxETH`","`tokensClaimed` is incremented by nominal token amount","Actual ETH received is lower than nominal in edge case","`WETH.deposit{value: tokensClaimed}` or payout accounting fails"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-023","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Dinero request IDs encode unbounded batch ranges that must be fully looped on finalization","locations":["withdraws/Dinero.sol:27","withdraws/Dinero.sol:31","withdraws/Dinero.sol:60","withdraws/Dinero.sol:75"],"claim":"Dinero request IDs store initial/final batch ids, and both `canFinalizeWithdrawRequest` and `_finalizeWithdrawImpl` iterate the full inclusive range without an upper bound.","impact":"Large multi-batch redemptions can exceed practical gas limits during finalize paths, making some requests difficult or impossible to finalize.","paths":["Large redemption spans many Dinero batches","Request stores wide initial-to-final batch range","Finalize flow loops entire range in readiness and execution paths","Gas usage grows with range and can exceed block limits"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-024","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Morpho migration can be underfunded by borrow-share rounding","locations":["routers/AbstractLendingRouter.sol:74","routers/AbstractLendingRouter.sol:232","routers/MorphoLendingRouter.sol:188","routers/MorphoLendingRouter.sol:192","routers/MorphoLendingRouter.sol:201","routers/MorphoLendingRouter.sol:224","routers/MorphoLendingRouter.sol:279"],"claim":"`migratePosition` seeds migration using old-router `healthFactor` borrowed assets (rounded down from shares), but Morpho full-exit repay path uses borrow shares and may require rounded-up assets in callback. The new router can approve/hold too little for the old router pull.","impact":"Migrations can revert for normal share/asset rounding cases, blocking router migrations and potentially trapping users on old routing paths.","paths":["User starts migration from a Morpho-backed position","New router computes borrow amount from old router `healthFactor`","Old router exits with `assetToRepay = type(uint256).max` (repay by shares)","Morpho callback requests slightly higher rounded-up assets","Transfer/allowance from new router is short and migration reverts"],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Pending withdraw requests not cleared on failed finalization","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`finalized == false` intentionally represents asynchronous pending state; this is expected behavior, not a distinct vulnerability."},{"title":"Division by zero in LP oracle when pool supply is zero","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Edge case is not realistically exploitable for protocol harm in active positions; when LP total supply is zero there is no collateralized LP exposure to value."},{"title":"Reward debt advances even when transfer fails silently","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing finding F-004."},{"title":"Pending withdraw valuation uses yield token price before finalization","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Overbroad generic claim; confirmed reportable case is manager-specific and captured as F-021 (Ethena cooldown)."},{"title":"No vault-lending router association validation in setPosition","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"By design, any whitelisted lending router may open positions on whitelisted vaults; no unauthorized vault write primitive is introduced beyond router whitelist trust."},{"title":"Permissionless manual finalization allows early ERC4626 conversion","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing finding F-013."},{"title":"Health factor uses account-agnostic vault price oracle","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Inaccurate as stated: `healthFactor` calls `price(borrower)` with borrower context. Broader oracle-path concern is already tracked in F-002."},{"title":"setCurrentAccount modifier lacks reentrancy protection","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Speculative; no concrete reentrant exploit path shown through router-gated call graph."},{"title":"Pendle PT slippage validation only applied to DEX trades","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Incorrect: direct redemption path checks `minPurchaseAmount` at `staking/PendlePT.sol:122`."},{"title":"AbstractSingleSidedLP pool share check compares against total supply","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Intended design check to cap protocol share of pool supply; no concrete bypass or harm demonstrated."},{"title":"Ethena cooldown holder allows duplicate cooldown initiation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Claim is unsupported; each request uses a fresh cloned holder and cooldown state is per-holder."},{"title":"Origin withdrawal request lacks validation for zero amount","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Low-value input hygiene and largely subsumed by existing dust/zero-yield withdraw edge case in F-005."},{"title":"RewardManagerMixin allows non-router to claim for any account","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"No value diversion: rewards are transferred to the target account, not caller; front-running alone does not create protocol-level loss."},{"title":"TimelockUpgradeableProxy upgrade state not cleared after execution","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing finding F-015."},{"title":"Dinero batch nonce uses unbounded increment","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing finding F-009."}]}
